task.summary: Default task
Added a .gitignore file
Began updating the way that models are stored (one PHP config file)
Refactored the way that models are initialized in the application; Changed the order of the logging function's parameters to make a little bit more sense.
Began update

Finished (hopefully) updating the way that relationships are made and models are configured. Still probably some stuff to do. Also updated the way the Log file logs and the ModelNotFoundException stores messages (allowing strings)
Fixed some aspects of the relationship part

Fixed a few paths in the require_js configuration. Migrated away from the "main" files to the new Entity loading system; created the SmEntity class, added a mechanism to populate its Models automatically, began removing the necessity of previously core files. Updated the way Sm.js loads files to prevent false alarms and uncalled functions. Made the process a little bit smoother.
Added a method to configure the Meta classes, reciprocal and non-reciprocal relationships are now separated. Updated the way that relationships are interpreted from the object.
Removed most of the "stub" files (files that were made only based on a template, not necessary any longer due to the updated relationship structure
non-reciprocal relationships now also can return models as long as the relationship is properly cloned.
Added a more generic body template, marked the existing templates as requirements
Can now convert ModelIterators directly to string, load from an array of Models for the Wrapper to be more aware of the relationships we have.
Added a more complete way of viewing relationships
Changed the way that actions are prompted. Added User-Page relationships. Updated the CSS to match the new style. Added a better way to delete multiple MvCombos
Can now prompt the creation of an entity while adding a new relationship
Can now create and use universes properly
Concepts are defaultively displayed as tags; can now view tags retrieved from select2; added "once" functionality to the Emitter class
Updated the way relationships are found
Added tag click events to select2
A way to prompt to edit relationships
There is now a process to automatically generate Modal dialogs
There is a way to categorize relationships by their subtype; positioned relationships are now indexed via list elements
COntinued working on the way relationships are added/entitities are dragged
Side project for Allenotes
